11:09 AM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing. Defendant Tiwanna R Williams in court.  Attorney Steven Hughes in court for Tiwanna R Williams.  Prosecuting attorney Abbey Nickolie in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Court notes the State has filed an Amended Information.  Atty. Hughes acknowledges receipt, waives reading and enters initial not guilty plea.  Court notes a plea questionnaire has been filed and recites the offer as listed in the document.  State and Defense confirm the offer.  State also notes they are in victim rights compliance and the victim is present in court today.  State also notes there is restitution being sought.  Defense is not contesting the amount of restitution.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant. Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1 of the Amended Information, Court finds defendant guilty. 

Victim presents statements.
Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Hughes.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

6 Months Jail Straight Time.

Term of Probation: 12 Months

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No contact with Firehouse subs and any individual listed in the Criminal Complaint.
-	Take Thinking for a Change Course;
-	Perform 25 Hours of Community Service;
-	Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended.  
-	Work with and through the Agent to return the property requested by the victim.

RESTITUTION: $3,581.31 to be paid to Firehouse Subs;

COSTS:  $253.00 (includes DRGOD surcharge);

DNA Surcharge: $200.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.
